						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Mostly, i'm just hoping this'll raise some awareness that you can use .incbin more flexibly in any project. </div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Waaaaat</div><br /><br />Mission accomplished! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> I figured after a search that this might not be well known. Easy to miss <br /> nice features when the sum of them are so extensive. <br /><br />---<br /><br />Another good thing is that you can always be sure that you're not breaking the ROM budget with a file that has been mistakenly padded. A recurring mistake i do is, when using NESST &gt; all &gt; save is that it defaults and pads the tilemap size to 8kB:s, rather than 4kB:s, which is the expected size in my workflow. <br /><br />Doing full tilemap inclusions like so:<br /><tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.incbin &quot;name.chr&quot;,0,$1000</tt><br />makes similar situations failsafe / human error less likely.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

